```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return strip(lowercase(replace(col, [" ", "-"] => "_")))
end
```

This function takes a `String` as input and returns the cleaned column name. It first strips any leading or trailing whitespaces using `strip()`, then lowercases the string with `lowercase()`, and finally replaces spaces and hyphens with underscores using `replace()`.
